Mutation Rules
•All mutations must call precheck_mutation_guard(region_id, feature_id="trips", mutation_class)
•trip_name, destination_summary, departure_date, return_date: mutable in DRAFT and PRE_TRIP_STRUCTURED states only via trip_field_updated event
•jurisdiction_ids: mutable until CLAIM_ROUTING_LOCKED via trip_jurisdiction_updated event
•itinerary_hash update triggers itinerary_version increment and trip_itinerary_changed event
•paid_unlock: set once via trip_unlock_confirmed event. Cannot be reversed.
•maturity_state: governed exclusively by Section 3.5 state machine. No direct field update.
•archived_at: set via trip_archived event. Once set, no further mutations permitted except via Founder override.

State Machine
Full state definitions in Section 3.5. Summary:
State	From	To	Guard Condition	Emitted Event
DRAFT	—	PRE_TRIP_STRUCTURED	Itinerary confirmed, no incident	trip_itinerary_confirmed
PRE_TRIP_STRUCTURED	DRAFT	INCIDENT_OPEN	Incident created (CCO instantiated)	trip_state_advanced
INCIDENT_OPEN	PRE_TRIP_STRUCTURED	DOCUMENTATION_IN_PROGRESS	Evidence attached	trip_state_advanced
DOCUMENTATION_IN_PROGRESS	INCIDENT_OPEN	CLAIM_ROUTING_LOCKED	User enters routing stage	trip_state_advanced
CLAIM_ROUTING_LOCKED	DOCUMENTATION…	CLAIM_SUBMITTED	Claim packet generated	trip_state_advanced
CLAIM_SUBMITTED	CLAIM_ROUTING_LOCKED	POST_TRIP_RESOLVED	Resolution confirmed	trip_state_advanced
POST_TRIP_RESOLVED	CLAIM_SUBMITTED	ARCHIVED	User or system archives	trip_archived

