Surge Behavior
•Under ELEVATED mode: Trip creation allowed. Itinerary confirmation allowed. Scan job creation rate-limited per account.
•Under PROTECTIVE mode: Trip creation allowed (core capability, never paywalled). Itinerary confirmation allowed. Deep Scan creation blocked. paid_unlock blocked pending queue.
•Under RECOVERY mode: Read-only. No new trip creation. Existing trips accessible. Mutations queued.
•Trip itinerary_hash lookup is cached. Identical hash returns cached Quick Scan result (account-bound, rate-limited) without new ScanJob creation.

Export Requirements
•Export profile TRAVELER_PERSONAL: full trip data, PII included, redaction_ruleset_version binding required
•Export profile INVESTOR: aggregated only, no individual trip_id, no PII
•Export profile AUDITOR: full trip data including ledger references, PII masked
•paid_unlock_at and created_by are always included in AUDITOR exports
•Export completeness manifest must include trip_id, maturity_state, itinerary_version

Data Retention & Compliance Sensitivity
PII Level	Medium — contains destination, dates, group membership. No passport data at this object level.
Retention	Active trips: retain indefinitely while account active. Archived trips: retain 7 years (financial record) then anonymize. [Placeholder — pending Section 8.x retention schedule]
GDPR Erasure	trip_name, destination_summary erasable. trip_id, created_at, ledger references retained per 3.2.0.1 placeholder doctrine.
Encryption	Encryption at rest via Supabase default (AES-256). Field-level encryption for destination data: pending Section 8.x encryption spec.

Replay Requirements
•Trip maturity_state must be reconstructable by replaying all trip_state_advanced events in ledger order
•itinerary_version must be reconstructable by counting trip_itinerary_changed events
•paid_unlock status must be reconstructable from trip_unlock_confirmed event presence
•No heuristic reconstruction permitted. All state derivable from event_ledger alone.

