3.2.6 — Object 5: Claim
🆕 NEW OBJECT REQUIRED  No `claims` table exists in any migration. This object must be created. The Claim object represents the traveler's intention to pursue a specific claim path — not the claim submitted to the insurer. The platform creates and manages structured claim preparation artifacts only.

Canonical Name	Claim
DB Table	claims — MISSING, creation required
Purpose	Represents a structured claim preparation artifact. The Claim is the output of the Claim Routing & Sequencing Engine (F-6.5.5). It does not submit claims to insurers. It organizes evidence, routing recommendations, and sequencing logic into a copy-only packet that the traveler uses to pursue their own claim.
Key Distinction	A Claim is not a submission. The platform never acts as a claims intermediary. The Claim object is a decision-support artifact only.
