3.2.11 — Object 10: ScanCreditLedger
🆕 NEW OBJECT REQUIRED  Section 10.2 defines 2 Deep Scan credits per paid trip unlock. No credit ledger table exists. This is a launch-blocking gap — credits cannot be enforced without this object.

Canonical Name	ScanCreditLedger
DB Table	scan_credit_ledger — MISSING, creation required
Purpose	Append-only ledger of credit grants and deductions per trip. The current balance is always computed by summing ledger rows (credits_delta). No stored balance field — balance is a derived value. This mirrors the event_ledger pattern.
Key Invariant	No UPDATE. No DELETE. Balance = SUM(credits_delta) WHERE trip_id = ?. Negative deductions record credit consumption. Positive entries record grants.

Field	Type	Immutable	Required	Description
entry_id	UUID	YES	YES	Immutable.
trip_id	UUID → trips	YES	YES	Immutable.
account_id	UUID	YES	YES	Immutable.
entry_type	text ENUM	YES	YES	grant | deduction | refund | expiry. Immutable.
credits_delta	integer	YES	YES	Positive = grant; negative = deduction. Immutable.
scan_id	UUID → scan_jobs	NO	NO	Linked ScanJob for deduction entries.
